The paper deals with modeling and calculating deformation fields between shapes, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The use of Karhunen-Lo\`eve expansion and volume-preserving deformation suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.GR (Graphics). The focus on shape correspondence and registration also suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible category. The use of optimization and downsampled versions of shapes suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as another possible category. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques such as Karhunen-Lo\`eve expansion suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category.
